column2: The underway data were collected at a total of 11 stations on the FV Elena Rosa cruise May 1997. These samples were taken around Eden| NSW to determine the bio-optical charateristics of the region. The data can be used for Ocean Colour sensor validation. Parameters measured are pigments.
data has been quality controlled by in-house procedures
A value of -999 means the pigment was not measured| while 0.000 means it was measured but below the detection limit.
High Performance Liquid Chromatography of pigments in discrete sea-water samples
